---
title: Maple and Rosemary-Glazed Pork Cutlets with Couscous and a Creamy Apple Salad
description: Apple and maple syrup may sound like ingredients for a breakfast or a baking recipe, but we’ve managed to work those flavors into a quick and simple pork dish. The maple syrup gets stirred into the sauce, coating each cutlet in sticky deliciousness. The apple, on the other hand, gives a fruity boost to the creamy side salad. And with hearty couscous to back up all those flavors, you’ve got nothing less than sweet, sweet perfection.
